The South African National Roads Agency has released a notice of a full road closure on the N3 in Howick and Lions River in the next few days. These road closures are part of the N2/N3 freeway upgrade programme. According to the report, all lanes will be closed from  March 7 to 9 from 10am to 12pm and again from 2pm to 4pm. “Routes that will be affected include the Northbound Howick/Midmar (Exit 103) interchange towards Johannesburg, and the Southbound Nottingham (Exit 132) interchange when travelling towards Durban or Pietermaritzburg,” read the statement. SANRAL has urged travellers to adjust their travel plans and to take alternative routes.